{
  "texts": [
    "Three-dimensional grid-based VAEs, which take cues from 3D image recognition, are the third kind of cutting-edge VAEs (Ji et al., 2012).",
    "Inherently, grids make learning from 3D spatial conformations via 3D convolutions easier.",
    "This relies heavily on 3D-CNN for both the encoder and decoder.",
    "The input data for a 3D grid-VAE model of molecules should likewise be in 3D.",
    "However, there is a dearth of readily accessible datasets for 3D Grid-VAE when compared to those utilized for training SMILES-VAE or Graph-VAE."
  ]
}